INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (3,1,'2007-04-12 22:58:24','2007-04-13 02:58:24','So, instead of posting some lame news section on the front page of all the Pooled sites (oh yah, there are three now &minus; see the sidebar), I decided I would throw up a quick Wordpress blog that I could post to instead.  That way, we get instant comments as well as cool stuff like RSS for all you feed reader people out there.\r\n\r\nI think the thing that I like best about a pool is the community behind it.  People start talking about picks, or bashing each other\'s Stanley cup teams, etc.  That kind of stuff makes it fun, not just for the few people who get paid out in the end :)\r\n\r\nAnyway, so I will try to post my development progress here as well as general Pooled-related news.  I plan to integrate the RSS feed from this blog into the main page of Pooled, so it will act as a bit of a news section as well.\r\n\r\nIf you want to leave comments, please use your username on the pool so people know who you are (and can check out your stats when they are up ;).  Obviously your emails are always kept private.','Pooled - The Blog',0,'','publish','open','open','','pooled-the-blog','','','2007-04-12 22:58:24','2007-04-13 02:58:24','',0,'http://phizero.net/pooled-blog/pooled-the-blog/',0,'post','',0),(2,1,'2007-04-12 21:50:19','2007-04-13 01:50:19','<p>I have been spending my free time (of which there has been admittedly less lately) developing a hockey pool for this year\'s playoffs.  I wanted to keep it simple and fun for everyone while promoting a bit of good old fashion rivalry.  The system is based on the rules of a hockey pool that I was involved in a few years back and I had a great time with it.  The rule system is simple:\r\n</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Everyone picks a right wing, center, left wing, two defense men and a goalie from the east and west conferences (so thats 12 player picks in total)</li>\r\n<li>You get to pick in rounds one, two and three -- for the fourth round you are stuck with the picks you made in the third round.\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>example: say theoretically that the <strikeout>leafs make the playoffs</strikeout>, you can pick all the leafs players you want in the first round, but because you get to re-pick in the second round, you can pick players from a better team because all your leaf\'s players got knocked out in the first round ;)</li>\r\n<li>At the beginning, you pick a team to win the stanley cup, you only get to pick once on this one.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>The point scheme is different on some of the pools, for my original instance of the pool (there are three for this year now) here is the point scheme:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>player goal - 1 point</li>\r\n	<li>player assist - 1 point</li>\r\n	<li>goalie win - 1 point</li>\r\n	<li>goalie shutout - 1 point</li>\r\n	<li>team wins cup - 5 points</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<p>So, that is pooled in a nutshell, feel free to keep up with this blog during the playoffs for updates.</p>','About Pooled',0,'','publish','open','open','','about','','','2007-04-12 22:44:21','2007-04-13 02:44:21','',0,'',0,'page','',0),(4,1,'2007-04-12 23:48:38','2007-04-13 03:48:38','<p>Okay, so you\'ve made your picks, the playoffs have started, but where are the stats? Well, this site has been a bit of a work in progress so not all the features are done yet. So, in order of importance, here is what I\'m working on:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Stats (leaderboard of everyone\'s points, possibly individual player stats)</li>\r\n	<li>Random picks for people who didn\'t make their picks at all or missed one or two players</li>\r\n	<li>A message board so you we yell at each other and this can be a real community</li>\r\n	<li>An RSS feed for the message board? for the leaderboard?</li>\r\n	<li>Probably a few other things I\'m missing but have written down somewhere...</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>I intend to at least finish the stats module this weekend, because you can\'t have a pool without knowing who you are beating ;)  So, please bear with me while I get it going.</p>\r\n<p>Is there anything that you guys want to see that I have missed?  If so, comment here and let me know.  If there seems to be a lot of people pushing for something, I will add it to the list of things to do.</p>\r\n','Where\'s the stats?',0,'','publish','open','open','','wheres-the-stats','','','2007-04-12 23:48:38','2007-04-13 03:48:38','',0,'http://phizero.net/pooled-blog/wheres-the-stats/',0,'post','',4),(5,1,'2007-04-16 01:34:19','2007-04-16 05:34:19','<p>After many people telling me to get my ass in gear, and others even resorting to name calling (all in good fun, of course), I have finally finished the stats portion of the pool.  It\'s a little rough around the edges right now, but it will do the trick.  There is a new menu item on the home page when you login that will take you there.  So, you can go get your stats fix right now if you want, but here is a sneak preview of the leaders from each pool:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Main Pool - Dre - 31pts</li>\r\n<li>Joel Pool - Cody - 30pts</li>\r\n<li>76design - Goats - 31pts</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The random picks have not been completed.  So, if you are among the few with incomplete or non-existent picks, you will have to wait to see what the random pick gods have in store for you.  I expect this to be done in the next few days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Oh, on a random note: the nhl.com database does not seem to have Jannik Hansen as an active member of the Canucks.  So, he had an assist tonight that won\'t help anyone out.  However, it doesn\'t really matter because since he wasn\'t in the nhl.com active player database then no one could have picked him anyway :P  I will make sure to get this fixed up for the next round, in case someone wants to pick him.</p>\r\n<p>Now I go to bed.</p>\r\n<p><em>Edit: oh yah, if you find any errors in the stats, comment here and I will fix them.  The output looked okay, and I hand verified one person, but there may be problems (I should have a perpetual beta notice or something).</em></p>','Unveiling of the stats',0,'','publish','open','open','','unveiling-of-the-stats','','','2007-04-16 01:36:05','2007-04-16 05:36:05','',0,'http://phizero.net/pooled-blog/unveiling-of-the-stats/',0,'post','',1),(6,1,'2007-04-17 19:52:09','2007-04-17 23:52:09','Stats are updated for last night\'s games.  Go Sens go!','Stats Updated',0,'','publish','open','open','','stats-updated','','','2007-04-17 19:52:09','2007-04-17 23:52:09','',0,'http://phizero.net/pooled-blog/stats-updated/',0,'post','',0),(7,1,'2007-04-19 23:43:44','2007-04-20 03:43:44','So, to all those poor souls who picked the Pens to win the cup, sorry \'bout yer luck!  Oh, and the stats have been updated up to last night, so none of tonight\'s games are on there.  Some people have really started pulling ahead in the pools!\r\n\r\nThat raises a question, do you think I should make the leader board and picks public, so you can see picks and points from users across all three pools?  Essentially, it would just show the leader board on the homepage of each pool without making people login.  Oh, and just so you know, the top user across all three pools right now is jyoung, he\'s at 52 points -- wouldn\'t you like to see who he picked?\r\n','Sorry Pens!',0,'','publish','open','open','','sorry-pens','','','2007-04-19 23:43:44','2007-04-20 03:43:44','',0,'http://phizero.net/pooled-blog/sorry-pens/',0,'post','',3),(8,1,'2007-04-23 20:05:31','2007-04-24 00:05:31','<p>Just as a clarification, the stats that were updated last night did not include the results from the Detroit - Calgary game because it was still in OT when I went to bed.  Everything is now up to date for all games in the first round except the Dallas - Vancouver game tonight.  I\'ve been hearing rumors from people that the points might be off slightly.  So, just so if any of you want to check the math, the point system is:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Goal, Assist, Goalie win - 1 point</li>\r\n<li>Goalie shutout - 2 points (for those of you in Joel\'s pool, its 3)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Post a comment here if you find any issues.</p>','Stats from yesterday',0,'','publish','open','open','','stats-from-yesterday','','','2007-04-23 20:05:31','2007-04-24 00:05:31','',0,'http://phizero.net/pooled-blog/stats-from-yesterday/',0,'post','',2),(9,1,'2007-04-24 00:58:07','2007-04-24 04:58:07','The stats have been updated to reflect Vancouver\'s win tonight. And since that is the end of the first round, you can also go make your picks for the second round starting now. I will keep the picks open until the puck drop -- which should be on Wednesday night. Good luck in the second round!','2nd Round Picks',0,'','publish','open','open','','2nd-round-picks','','','2007-04-24 00:58:07','2007-04-24 04:58:07','',0,'http://phizero.net/pooled-blog/2nd-round-picks/',0,'post','',3),(10,1,'2007-05-01 08:53:41','2007-05-01 12:53:41','<p>Yeah, I\'ve been slacking.  The stats haven\'t been updated since the end of the first round.  So, Dre was nice enough to slave over a calculator for a while and come up with the unofficial stats thus far (and then point out how lonely it is at the top).  I\'m not sure when these were actually calculated, but they were posted April 30th, 2007 at 6:49 pm, so I assume they don\'t include last night\'s games.</p>\r\n<p>I will make sure to update the stats tonight, and also work on automating the updates so that I don\'t have to keep apologizing.  Anyway, thanks Dre!</p>\r\n<blockquote><p>Unnoficial Second round stats to date: (I got bored)</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Dre - 85</li>\r\n	<li>Trish - 81</li>\r\n	<li>Jay - 78</li>\r\n	<li>Darkblaidd - 78</li>\r\n	<li>Daveyc - 77</li>\r\n	<li>Steve - 76</li>\r\n	<li>Atomic - 74</li>\r\n	<li>Scroggdog - 74</li>\r\n	<li>Mapleleafs - 73</li>\r\n	<li>Seanb - 73</li>\r\n	<li>Jclouthi - 72</li>\r\n	<li>Bcyr - 72</li>\r\n	<li>Jaymoe - 70</li>\r\n	<li>Apullin - 68</li>\r\n	<li>Colin - 64</li>\r\n	<li>Doogie - 60</li>\r\n	<li>Kevinp - 58</li>\r\n	<li>Sens Chug Bone - 50</li>\r\n	<li>Ddawg - 38</li>\r\n	<li>Frozenpuck - 8</li>\r\n	<li>Ph - 0</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>As you can see Iâ€™m back on top where I should be. Fucking lucky piece of shit Marty Turco and his crappy 3 shutouts. *ahem*</p>\r\n<p>Itâ€™s lonely at the top. But itâ€™s comforting to look down upon everyone at the bottom.</p></blockquote>','Dre does my work for me',0,'','publish','open','open','','dre-does-my-work-for-me','','','2007-05-01 08:53:41','2007-05-01 12:53:41','',0,'http://phizero.net/pooled-blog/dre-does-my-work-for-me/',0,'post','',2),(11,1,'2007-05-02 01:49:12','2007-05-02 05:49:12','<p>The stats are updated as of tonight, not including the Anaheim / Vancouver game.  I\'ve also changed the way things look a bit but nothing drastic, just a bit of a rearrange.</p>\r\n<p>The stats parsing script is much closer to being totally automated, not quite there yet, but definitely closer than it was.  Anyway, I\'m off to bed.</p>','Stats Updated',0,'','publish','open','open','','stats-updated-2','','','2007-05-02 01:49:12','2007-05-02 05:49:12','',0,'http://phizero.net/pooled-blog/stats-updated-2/',0,'post','',2),(12,1,'2007-05-02 23:24:44','2007-05-03 03:24:44','<p>I made a pretty simple modification to my stats parsing script that reduces my work by about 3 steps for each game I want to update.  So, I am able to get the updates done in a lot less time now, which means that the stats will be updated much more often (* you don\'t have to work very hard to update more than once a week ;) The next step is to get this thing updating totally automatically so I don\'t need to touch it, but that is probably another few hours of perl hacking for me.</p>\r\n<p>Anyway, the stats are up to date for tonight as of 10:45, so that doesn\'t include the Detroit / San Jose game. All the pools are pretty close, its going to be interesting to see what happens when it comes down to the wire.</p>','Stats now much easier to update',0,'','publish','open','open','','stats-now-much-easier-to-update','','','2007-05-02 23:24:44','2007-05-03 03:24:44','',0,'http://phizero.net/pooled-blog/stats-now-much-easier-to-update/',0,'post','',2),(13,1,'2007-05-08 23:46:55','2007-05-09 03:46:55','<p>The picks for the third round are now open.  You have until Thursday at 7pm to get them in (puck drop of the Ottawa/Buffalo series).  Remember that you <strong>do not</strong> get to pick new players for the fourth round, so you are stuck with what you pick now for the rest of the playoffs.  Also, we have to decide how many points we want the cup-winner pick to be.  I am thinking something drastic (like 10 or 20 points), just to make it interesting.</p>\r\n<p>I have also made some changes to the leader board stats.  You can now see how many spots you have moved up (or down) with the new update as well as the number of points you have gained since the last update.</p>\r\n<p>On another note: for pooled.phizero.net users, I need to get money from you.</p>','Third round picks open',0,'','publish','open','open','','third-round-picks-open','','','2007-05-08 23:46:55','2007-05-09 03:46:55','',0,'http://phizero.net/pooled-blog/third-round-picks-open/',0,'post','',2),(14,1,'2007-05-13 23:43:35','2007-05-14 03:43:35','<p>The stats have been updated to reflect all games played in the third round so far.  This includes the Detroit / Anaheim game tonight.</p>','Stats Updated',0,'','publish','open','open','','stats-updated-3','','','2007-05-13 23:43:35','2007-05-14 03:43:35','',0,'http://phizero.net/pooled-blog/stats-updated-3/',0,'post','',0),(15,1,'2007-05-17 23:20:58','2007-05-18 03:20:58','The stats have been updated to include the results of all games up until the Det / Ana game tonight.  If it is done before I go to bed (currently has 10mins left Ana up 4-3) then I will update it again tonight.\r\n\r\nHave a good long weekend everyone.  Go Sens!','Stats Updated',0,'','publish','open','open','','stats-updated-4','','','2007-05-17 23:20:58','2007-05-18 03:20:58','',0,'http://phizero.net/pooled-blog/stats-updated-4/',0,'post','',1),(16,1,'2007-06-07 23:27:57','2007-06-08 03:27:57','<p>Alright, all pools have been updated to reflect the entire playoffs.  The winners of each pool are as follows:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Pooled - Dre (199 pts)</li>\r\n	<li>76design Pool - kgreen (196 pts)</li>\r\n	<li>Joel\'s Pool - island (192 pts)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>As for the winners collecting their prizes.  No one from the \'Pooled\' pool (pooled.phizero.net) paid me, so no one gets paid (I probably could have been a bit more proactive on collecting money).  As for the other pools:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Joel you are in charge of yours so you can distribute the winnings as winner-take-all, some kind of tiered system or whatever.</li>\r\n	<li>76design will be settled in the office with a heated debate</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>I think things went pretty well this year, but this being the first year for this pool, there are many things that I would do differently.  Overall its been a good learning experience though and I hope to bring it back for next year with the edges smoothed out a bit.  Thanks to everyone for putting up with the long delays in updates and the mysterious random picks that never happened ;)  I hope to see everyone back next year.</p>\r\n<p>I have a few things that I plan on doing:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Make a big list of features / things that need polishing and slowly pick away at them.</li>\r\n	<li>Package up the code and publish it for download -- not that it would be of great use to anyone, but I know of a few people who may be interested.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>I\'ll be keeping this blog updated randomly so watch your feed readers if you use them.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Sens in \'08!!</strong></p>','All Pools Updated - Pool Complete',0,'','publish','open','open','','all-pools-updated-pool-complete','','','2007-06-07 23:27:57','2007-06-08 03:27:57','',0,'http://phizero.net/pooled-blog/all-pools-updated-pool-complete/',0,'post','',3),(17,1,'2008-04-10 14:18:23','2008-04-10 18:18:23','Starting up again for 2008. People have already made picks, but we need to decide on a points scheme. Check out the current points scheme on the about page here:\r\n\r\nhttp://phizero.net/pooled-blog/about\r\n\r\nLet me know what you think in the comments.','Thoughts on the point scheme?',0,'','publish','open','open','','thoughts-on-the-point-scheme','','','2008-04-10 14:18:23','2008-04-10 18:18:23','',0,'http://phizero.net/pooled-blog/thoughts-on-the-point-scheme/',0,'post','',1);
